  "summary": "onboardconnect-agent posts environment data to attacker-controlled Cloudflare Workers endpoint at install time",
  "details": "The package's dist/setup.js issues a fetch/POST at install/setup time to https://oc-worker-tenant-api.wpolanco.workers.dev carrying values from process.env, an attacker-controlled Cloudflare Workers endpoint not associated with any documented vendor publisher. dist/server.js contains additional POST calls and an outbound ping primitive (line 509). dist/crypto.js and dist/store.js use Buffer.from(..., 'base64') decoding consistent with payload/string obfuscation. The combination of an install/setup-time outbound POST to a personal Cloudflare Workers subdomain that exfiltrates environment variables is a hardcoded C2 exfiltration shape against the installer.",
